pr_review_body:
This makes sense to me. It would be good to add a test that triggers `dummies_needed`. Can we add a contrast to a model test, e.g.,

```JSON
{
  "Name": "explicit-contrast",
  "Level": "Dataset",
  "GroupBy": [],
  "Model": {"X": ["gain"], "Type": "glm"}
  "DummyContrasts": {"Test": "t"}
}
```

```JSON
{
  "Edges": [
    {
      "Source": "subject",
      "Destination": "explicit-contrast",
      "Filter": {"contrast": ["gain"]}
    }
  ]
}
```

I love the idea of documenting the database schema, but I don't like that it's all hand written in swagger. (And is missing a couple of columns and relationships)

Here's an [auto-generated version of the same diagram](https://gist.github.com/omad/2acc9d2e2139b4351442c2debf525158
) using [SchemaSpy](https://schemaspy.org/). It contains both the  `.dot` format which can be used with the Sphinx Graphviz extension. Or probably better, is to use the generated `svg`  directly, and include documentation next to it for updating the diagram if necessary.

